data.content:
Three things break. Here's each issue and the fix:

---

### 1. `ExecuteUpdateAsync` — expression tree no longer compiles

EF Core 10 added a non-expression `Func<>` overload. Your `Expression<Func<...>>` code won't compile due to overload ambiguity — and is no longer needed. Replace the entire block:

```csharp
await context.Blogs.ExecuteUpdateAsync(s =>
{
    s.SetProperty(b => b.Views, 8);
    if (nameChanged)
    {
        s.SetProperty(b => b.Name, "foo");
    }
});
```

No more manual expression trees.

---

### 2. Complex type columns — names change in two ways

**a) Sibling complex types with same property names** now get uniquified (e.g., two `Street` columns become `Street` and `Street1`). Pin the old names explicitly:

```csharp
modelBuilder.Entity<Customer>(b =>
{
    b.ComplexProperty(c => c.ShippingAddress,
        p => p.Property(a => a.Street).HasColumnName("Street"));
    b.ComplexProperty(c => c.BillingAddress,
        p => p.Property(a => a.Street).HasColumnName("Street"));
});
```

**b) Nested complex types** now use the full path. `Order.Payment.BillingAddress.City` previously mapped to column `BillingAddress_City`; it now maps to `Payment_BillingAddress_City`. To keep the old name:

```csharp
modelBuilder.Entity<Order>()
    .ComplexProperty(o => o.Payment)
    .ComplexProperty(p => p.BillingAddress)
    .Property(a => a.City)
    .HasColumnName("BillingAddress_City");
```

> **Either** pin column names as shown, **or** generate a migration and apply the rename to your database.

---

### 3. `IRelationalCommandDiagnosticsLogger` — new `logCommandText` parameter

Every method gains a `string logCommandText` parameter (contains redacted SQL for logging). Add it:

```csharp
public InterceptionResult<DbDataReader> CommandReaderExecuting(
    IRelationalConnection connection,
    DbCommand command,
    DbContext context,
    Guid commandId,
    Guid connectionId,
    DateTimeOffset startTime,
    string logCommandText)   // ← new parameter
{
    // Use logCommandText for log output (constants redacted)
    // Use command.CommandText for actual SQL
}
```

Update **all** methods on the interface (`CommandReaderExecuted`, `CommandScalarExecuting`, etc.) the same way.
